The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Okoro hits back
                                                                                                                                                                                                     Okoro hits back
            A STAFF REPORTER                      
	Calcutta: Mike Okoro was hurt after teammate Naseem Akhtar questioned his commitment. On Friday he almost single-handedly scripted Mohammedan Sportings victory against Mahindra United.         
	I have been playing in India for a long time I never expected this would ever happen to me Somebody will question my commitment the Nigerian said on Friday.         
	Asked whether Naseem said sorry for his comments, Okoro said: No he did not say that He only came and congratulated me. But I am not bothered about all these. I will play my game I wont let these things affect my game.                                                                                                                          
